The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, September 05, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Durgapur, Sept. 4: A teacher was arrested last night in connection with the death of 10-year-old Aditya Jadav, a Class III student of his school who drowned in a pond.

 Aditya went to bathe in the pond yesterday with 12 residential students of the school in Jamuria, 230 km from Calcutta. His father Chotu, an ECL employee, told police that the teacher, Ram Narayan Lal, forced him to take a dip.

 Suri: Three tourists were found dead in Tarapith on Sunday. Police said excessive drinking could have killed them.




